abstract="A ``smart city'' is generally meant as a technologically advanced cities, capable of joining ``competitiveness'' and ``sustainability'', by integrating different dimensions of development (economic, mobility, environment, people, living and governance), becoming self-sufficient. A broad definition that suggested different and varied visions, from which are derived identification systems and different classifications of Smart cities.",
