address="Cham",
pages="15--24",
abstract="The ability to recognize human activities from sensed information become more attractive to computer science researchers due to a demand on a high quality and low cost of health care services at anytime and anywhere. In this work, we proposed a new hybrid classification model to perform automatic recognition of activities in a smart home using KNN-WSVM combined the K-Nearest Neighbors (KNN) with Weighted Support Vector Machines (WSVM) learning algorithm, allowing to better discrimination between the classes of activity. We also added the temporal features (TF) in the used method KNN-WSVM. Experiments show our proposed approach outperforms the KNN, WSVM used alone in terms of recognition performance, highlighting the advantages of this method.",
