abstract="The cost and complexity of healthcare delivery to a globally ageing population is driving developments in the field of assistive living technologies. This paper focuses on the concept and the system infrastructure of the MiiHome project, which assists person-centered integrated care in the home. Working closely with a care organization delivering integrated health and social care and the housing sector, the MiiHome project aims to prevent problems before they escalate to the detriment of the person by using digital technologies.",
