year="2019",
publisher="Springer International Publishing",
address="Cham",
pages="17--27",
abstract="This article presents the use of the remote computing resources for the face recognition process as a part of a ``smart'' home security system. Such approach allows us to optimize the load of the computation resources and to reduce the price of security system by using non-powerful hardware and to run high load face recognition calculations on the remote server of the service provider. Article describes different cases of face recognition usage, combined with the manual user interactions for better reliability of the security system.",
isbn="978-3-030-01069-0",
url_article="https://link.springer.com/chapter/10.1007/978-3-030-01069-0_2"
