abstract="The term ``e-health'' was born in 1999 to represent the provision of healthcare services through Internet [11], and was heavily promoted by the industry and commercial sectors in order to take advantage of the power and excitement that other ``e-'' terms like e-commerce and e-business had recently created in society [8, 6]. Nevertheless, the academic world would soon adopt it, leading to what some authors call ``the death of telemedicine'' [14].",
