abstract="Useful information about person's behavior and its changes provides the measurement of the physical activity of the monitored person in flat. The identified changes are cyclic with a period of approximately 24 hours -- this is Circadian Rhythm of Activity, CAR. In the event that we correlate CAR with information about the type of room and activities envisaged in this room, we can define the circadian rhythm (CR). The CR evaluation is made by different mathematical and statistical procedures now. Such systems do not mostly have predictive character.",
